<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Bayern Munich manager Hans-Dieter Flick has congratulated Liverpool on the £25million signing of Thiago Alcantara.</p>

<p>Having been linked with the Spaniard all summer, Liverpool finally made a breakthrough in their negotiations with Bayern on Thursday after they agreed to pay a minimum of £20m over the next four years, along with £5m in add-ons.</p>

<p>The 29-year-old was made available by Bayern after he entered the final year of his contract, which saw the European champions cash in on arguably their best midfielder.</p>

<p>Bayern Munich boss Hans-Dieter Flick has congratulated Liverpool on signing Thiago</p>

<p>Thiago, who starred in Bayern's Champions League triumph, will move in a £25m deal</p>

<p>And now with his move agreed between the two clubs, Flick took the opportunity to heap praise on Thiago, while applauding Liverpool for their most recent acquisition. </p>

<p>'Thiago is an extraordinary player and was very important for us,' Flick said. 'My coaching team and I enjoyed working with him.</p>

<p>'It was very emotional as we said goodbye. I can only congratulate Liverpool as they got a great player and especially a great person.</p>

<p>'Thiago gave the team a lot of options and made us unpredictable, he solved things in ways you don't expect.</p>

<p>Flick (left) heaped praise on the Spanish midfielder after his move to Anfield was confirmed</p>

<p>'Now we're losing yet another great player. We are in contact with Hasan [Salihamidzic, sporting director] and we are confident that we can still do something.</p>

<p>'We're positive and we have the first game tomorrow. That's the focus now and we have a good squad with which we can win the game.'</p>

<p>Thiago will join Liverpool on a four-year deal and will wear the No 6 shirt, as he has done all through his career. </p>
